commentMessage: I don't think this is correct. The CLR run, without running the training & inference with no CLR, gives pretty bad accuracy of 98.65% and a baseline error of 2.32%. Something is passed on from the first training run without CLR if you have both tests at the same time.
What is the need of window( optimal learning rate range)  for learning rate when you have already plotted all learning rate vs/ accuracy plot.
